news.title: Holcim to sell Brazilian business to CSN in $1 billion deal
news.para: Holcim is trying to diversify away from its core business of cement and aggregates to focus more on building technology as it increases its emphasis on sustainability.

news.title: USA: In a hot market, companies compete with would-be homeowners
news.para: Residential real estate bought by companies or institutions hit an all-time high of 67,943 properties in the second quarter, according to Redfin, a Seattle-based online brokerage.

news.title: Arvind SmartSpaces raises Rs 85 crore from investors
news.para: Sanjay Lalbhai, chairman of Arvind SmartSpaces said, "This infusion of long term patient capital into the company will give us the flexibility to pursue strategic growth across all the segments that we operate in."

news.title: Chandigarh finance secretary letter to EO for keeping rules in abeyance not acceptable: SC
news.para: The Supreme Court made these observations while providing relief to city residents who were seeking conversion of leasehold residential sites into freehold.

news.title: Reserve price for Air India office in Nagpur lowered to Rs 33 crore
news.para: The reserve price for the office — spread in an area of 27,200 square feet — has been lowered by 10% to Rs 33.3 crore. In the first round, the base price was fixed at Rs 37 crore.

news.title: Pune: Lookout notices for Narayan Rane's wife, MLA son over Rs 65 crore unpaid loans
news.para: The LOCs have been authorised by three parties, including the Union Home Ministry, the lender, and the financial institution (Dewan Housing Finance Ltd), followed by a complaint by Maharashtra government on August 20.

news.title: Coimbatore corporation's engineers, TP officials to stop building plan violations together
news.para: The town planning section is responsible for approving building plans, regularising them and clearing encroachments. The section is short staffed to meet the workload prevailing in the city, sources said.

news.title: Property tax amnesty scheme for residents living in Lal Dora, other areas: NDMC
news.para: The NDMC has rolled out a new amnesty scheme in order to provide relief to the residents living in areas falling within Lal Dora, extended Lal Dora, extended 'abadi' of village and 544 unauthorised regularised colonies and unauthorised colonies and properties allotted to the Kashmiri migrants, officials said.

news.title: Mutation doesn't give property ownership right: Supreme Court
news.para: A bench of Justices M R Shah and Aniruddha Bose said an entry in revenue records does not confer title on a person whose name appears in record-of-rights.

news.title: LIC Housing raises over Rs 2,335 crore by issuing preference shares to LIC
news.para: The company has allotted 4,54,00,000 equity shares on a preferential basis to Life Insurance Corporation of India (LIC), the housing finance firm said in a regulatory filing.

news.title: About 1,800 Amrapali buyers including Dhoni told to clear balance amount in 15 days
news.para: ​The allotment of flats booked by these homebuyers will be "automatically cancelled" if the flat owners fail to register their name in Customer Data maintained by the court receiver and also do not start making payment within 15 days from the public notice issued on Thursday.

news.title: SIT visits Supertech Emerald Court to gather details
news.para: The group spent 20 minutes at Aster 2 – the building closest to the twin towers and most affected by their construction – to speak to some of its residents.

news.title: China Evergrande bonds rebound as loan payment extensions ease default worries
news.para: CITIC dispatched a small team to Shenzhen, where Evergrande is based, last week, but it is not optimistic that Evergrande's liquidity will improve soon, the source added, citing difficulties in finding buyers for its assets and the country's strict mortgage policies.

news.title: Apartment prices in Greece rise 4.6% in Q2 2021
news.para: Property accounts for a big chunk of household wealth in Greece, where the home ownership rate is about 73.5%, above the euro zone average of 66%, according to European Union statistics on income and living conditions.

news.title: Submit plan to utilise 25-acre vacant land in Chandigarh sectors 52 & 56: Adviser
news.para: During a meeting on Wednesday, sources revealed that urban planning department proposed to develop commercial area and green cover on the land.
